<TITLE> Ministry to consult BERC on energy prices </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 15 (bdnews24.com)The energy ministry will continue to fix fuel prices, taking into account the opinion of the regulators BERC, a high-level meeting decided Wednesday. "From now on, the ministry will consult the BERC before deciding on prices," energy secretary Mohammad Mohsin told bdnews24.com after a meeting with the regulators. The decision followed a dispute between the ministry and the BERC, with the latter citing the law that gave the regulators the powers to fix prices of all energy products. The meeting, convened mainly to discuss amendments to the Bangladesh Energy Regulatory Commission (BERC) Act 2003, also dealt with proposed changes to educational requirements for the commission' top jobs. BERC chairman Golam Rahman, commissioners, law ministry officials also attended the meeting chaired by the energy secretary. 
